text: Isaiah Firebrace (born 21 November 1999) is an Australian singer. He won the eighth season of The X Factor Australia in 2016. He then represented his country at the Eurovision Song Contest in 2017 with the song "Don't Come Easy". He finished 9th in the contest. In 2016, he released his first studio album, Isaiah. It peaked at number 12 on the ARIA Charts. Firebrace was born in Portland, Victoria. He grew up in Moama, New South Wales.
